From e9811a740de52335d575c8d86034f53cd5fd8781 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Deng, Bing" <bing.deng@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 14:49:49 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add profiling instrumentation, new LiDAR configs, and thread
 tuning

Features:
1. Add avia_ros2.yaml, targeting the FAST-LIO2 paper's Avia setup
   (1000m map cube, 0.5m voxel, point_filter_num=4).
2. Add avia_ros2_remote.yaml for the mujoco_bridge simulator, which
   publishes plain x/y/z/intensity clouds instead of Avia's CustomMsg.
3. Add config/velodyne_generic.yaml, a Velodyne HDL-32E parameter set
   for NCLT validation in the fast-lio2-demo pipeline, with the
   LiDAR-IMU extrinsic derived from the NCLT dataset paper's own
   Table 4 sensor calibration (Carlevaris-Bianco et al. 2016) rather
   than the UrbanLoco/Point-LIO placeholder it started from.
4. Gate a per-frame latency CSV (Log/fast_lio_profiling.csv) behind a
   new ENABLE_PROFILING cmake option; release builds are unaffected.
5. Log timing for h_share_model's transform/kdtree/plane stages and
   the EKF's manifold/kalman/cov/dx-solve/boxplus/converge/h_dyn_share
   steps, plus odom publish time, raw point count, and queue wait.
6. Detect and log lidar frame skips (gaps over 1.5x the scan period).
7. Let MP_PROC_NUM be overridden via a cmake cache variable, and raise
   the x86 auto-detected default from 3 to 4 threads on >4-core boxes.
8. Upgrade to C++17 and make the Python dependency optional, matching
   Jazzy/Humble RCLCPP requirements.

Performance:
1. Move per-stage algorithm timers to CLOCK_MONOTONIC so a PTP clock
   step (phc2sys) can no longer corrupt a latency measurement.
2. Write the profiling CSV from a lock-free ring buffer drained by a
   dedicated thread, off the LiDAR callback's hot path; pad the
   ring's head/tail counters to avoid false sharing, and pin the
   writer to a core outside the algorithm's cpuset.
3. Skip the fout_pre debug-log write entirely when runtime_pos_log
   is off, instead of writing it unconditionally.

Bug fixes:
1. Check for a 'time' field before reading it in velodyne_handler, to
   avoid a segfault on point clouds without per-point time.
2. Create Log/ before opening pos_log.txt or the profiling CSV, and
   guard fclose(fp) with a null check, so a missing directory or an
   unopened file can't crash startup/shutdown.
3. Stop linking PythonLibs unconditionally so the build doesn't fail
   on systems without Python dev headers installed.
4. Revert UrbanLoco's fov_degree to 180; the field is unused in the
   codebase, so 360 only caused confusion.
5. Replace velodyne_generic.yaml's identity LiDAR-IMU extrinsic (an
   UrbanLoco/Point-LIO placeholder) with the real Velodyne HDL-32E ->
   Microstrain MS25 IMU transform, composed from the NCLT paper's own
   Table 4 body-frame sensor poses (x_body_vel, x_body_imu) - the
   placeholder's identity rotation was off by ~90 degrees of yaw from
   the actual mounting.

Signed-off-by: Deng, Bing <bing.deng@intel.com>
